[ ] introduce ActionsFile as the workspace-layer file type  $ ActionsFile { path: PathBuf, actions: Vec<SourcedAction> } replaces ActionList = Vec<Action> as the type returned by file I/O; ActionList stays as a pure domain alias $ #019e513a-db99-762b-ba3f-68b844101e03
    >[ ] extend SourcedAction to carry source range  $ add range: Option<SourceRange> to SourcedAction — absorbs what Action.source was holding for LSP diagnostics $ #019e513a-db99-7ce7-987e-fed03998d32a
    >[ ] strip source from domain Action  $ remove source: Option<SourceMetadata> from domain/mod.rs Action struct — file position is not a domain concern $ #019e513a-db99-70c0-8f33-24e20e239d0f
    >[ ] update workspace/store load path to produce ActionsFile, then convert to domain  $ load_domain_model converts ActionsFile → Action at the boundary; sidecar hydration happens here before conversion, not after $ #019e513a-db99-7b46-b41a-f18d2643ac73
[ ] introduce ICSPlan as the workspace-layer file type for plans  $ ICSPlan { path: PathBuf, uid: String, plan: Plan } — distinguishes the ICS file from the domain Plan it represents $ #019e513a-db99-7a27-aae3-f27daae5e152
[ ] align MarkdownCharter with the pattern  $ already exists — audit From conversions and ensure file fields never reach graph or domain consumers $ #019e513a-db99-7702-bbf5-277dd4513856
[ ] move sidecar hydration to workspace boundary  $ hydrate_acts currently mutates after domain construction; move it to pre-conversion in load path so domain types are never in a partially-hydrated state $ #019e513a-db99-7b2f-9b8c-07b9fbc9e29f
[ ] de-publicise _for_workspace inference functions  $ infer_charter_name_for_workspace, infer_parent_charter_name_for_workspace, infer_plan_charter_name_for_workspace, infer_plan_parent_for_workspace are only called internally — change to pub(crate) $ #019e513a-db99-7d78-893b-b9ad14ac6f9a
[ ] rationalise workspace/mod.rs re-exports  $ after file types are introduced, align re-exports so callers use a single access pattern rather than mixing workspace::ics::* with top-level re-exports $ #019e513a-db99-748a-aedc-a97a36c2dcfa
